parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk or lunge, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts harshly
the vehicle jerks or lunges
the transmission fails to shift into gear
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the throttle and transmission lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine idle RPM surges
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the throttle body warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve body can cause the transmission to shift harshly, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts harshly
the vehicle jerks or lunges
the transmission fails to shift into gear
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the loss of essential vehicle information, such as speed, RPM, and fuel level, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The instrument panel goes dark
gauges stop functioning
reverse lights stay on
vents won't work
and the dashboard gauges are off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the engine to shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle loses power
and the throttle pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including the loss of power, lights, and other essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The radio won't work
windows won't work
sunroof won't work
and the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause the loss of power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle loses power
and the safety mode feature is initiated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall, surge, or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents, especially when entering or exiting highways or busy intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the vehicle surges forward when parked or in gear
the vehicle accelerates on its own
the vehicle loses power while driving
the "Failed Safe Mode" error message appears on the dashboard
the wrench warning light illuminates on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the accelerator pedal is depressed but the vehicle fails to accelerate
the "Failsafe Engine Mode" warning is displayed on the message board
the vehicle jerks or surges forward while idling
the engine throttles up and then stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling and Failsafe Engine Mode
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle and activation of the "Failsafe Engine Mode" can cause the vehicle to lose power and accelerate suddenly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the "Failsafe Engine Mode" warning is displayed on the message board
the accelerator pedal is depressed but the vehicle fails to accelerate
the vehicle jerks or surges forward while idling
the engine throttles up and then stalls.
